## Goal

Implement the three pre-confirmation validators (`pendingValidator`, `attestationValidator`, `rejectionValidator`) in the Firecat protocol library and wire them into the schema. These validators enforce the write-once, type-safe rules for the confirmation flow's first two stages.

## Background

The CONFIRMATION.md design document (`libs/firecat-protocol/CONFIRMATION.md`) specifies four new URI programs:

```
immutable://pending/{contentHash}/{submitterNodeKey}    -> hash://sha256/{envelopeHash}
immutable://attestation/{envelopeHash}/{nodeKey}        -> true
immutable://rejection/{envelopeHash}/{nodeKey}          -> string (reason)
immutable://confirmation/{contentHash}/{envelopeHash}   -> true
```

This story implements the first three. The `confirmationValidator` is separate (G2-A2-02) because it requires `list()` access which is not part of the standard `ValidationFn` signature and needs a design decision.

The existing validators in `libs/firecat-protocol/validators.ts` (`balanceValidator`, `consumedValidator`, `genesisValidator`, `consensusRecordValidator`) follow a consistent pattern: write-once check, value type check, referential integrity check.

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] `pendingValidator` exported from `libs/firecat-protocol/validators.ts`
  - [ ] Rejects if URI already exists (write-once)
  - [ ] Rejects if value is not a string starting with `hash://sha256/`
  - [ ] Rejects if referenced envelope (`read(value)`) does not exist
  - [ ] Accepts valid pending writes
- [ ] `attestationValidator` exported from `libs/firecat-protocol/validators.ts`
  - [ ] Rejects if URI already exists (write-once, prevents equivocation)
  - [ ] Rejects if value is not `true`
  - [ ] Rejects if envelope hash (extracted from URI) does not exist at `hash://sha256/{envelopeHash}`
  - [ ] Accepts valid attestation writes
- [ ] `rejectionValidator` exported from `libs/firecat-protocol/validators.ts`
  - [ ] Rejects if URI already exists (write-once)
  - [ ] Rejects if value is not a non-empty string
  - [ ] Rejects if envelope hash (extracted from URI) does not exist at `hash://sha256/{envelopeHash}`
  - [ ] Accepts valid rejection writes
- [ ] All three validators are registered in `libs/firecat-protocol/mod.ts` schema
- [ ] `CONFIRMATION_THRESHOLD` and `ATTESTATION_TIMEOUT_MS` added to `libs/firecat-protocol/constants.ts`
- [ ] Comprehensive tests in `libs/firecat-protocol/validators_test.ts`
- [ ] Existing validator tests still pass

## Implementation Guide

1. Read `libs/firecat-protocol/CONFIRMATION.md` sections 2 and 3 for the validator specifications.

2. Read `libs/firecat-protocol/validators.ts` to understand the existing pattern (especially `consumedValidator` which is structurally similar).

3. Add helper function to extract URI segments:
   ```typescript
   /** Extract path segment at index from URI: immutable://program/seg0/seg1/seg2 */
   function extractSegment(uri: string, index: number): string | null {
     const url = URL.parse(uri);
     if (!url) return null;
     const segments = url.pathname.substring(1).split("/");
     return segments[index] ?? null;
   }
   ```

4. Implement `pendingValidator`:
   ```typescript
   export const pendingValidator: ValidationFn = async ({ uri, value, read }) => {
     // Write-once
     const existing = await read(uri);
     if (existing.success) {
       return { valid: false, error: "Already pending" };
     }
     // Value must be envelope hash reference
     if (typeof value !== "string" || !value.startsWith("hash://sha256/")) {
       return { valid: false, error: "Value must be envelope hash URI" };
     }
     // Envelope must exist
     const envelope = await read(value);
     if (!envelope.success) {
       return { valid: false, error: "Referenced envelope not found" };
     }
     return { valid: true };
   };
   ```

5. Implement `attestationValidator` and `rejectionValidator` following the same pattern (see CONFIRMATION.md section 3).

6. Add constants to `libs/firecat-protocol/constants.ts`:
   ```typescript
   export const CONFIRMATION_THRESHOLD = 2;
   export const ATTESTATION_TIMEOUT_MS = 60_000;
   ```

7. Register in `libs/firecat-protocol/mod.ts`:
   ```typescript
   "immutable://pending": pendingValidator,
   "immutable://attestation": attestationValidator,
   "immutable://rejection": rejectionValidator,
   ```

8. Write tests using `MemoryClient` to seed state and verify each validator's accept/reject paths.

## Files to Create/Modify

- `libs/firecat-protocol/validators.ts` -- Add `pendingValidator`, `attestationValidator`, `rejectionValidator`, and `extractSegment` helper.
- `libs/firecat-protocol/constants.ts` -- Add `CONFIRMATION_THRESHOLD`, `ATTESTATION_TIMEOUT_MS`.
- `libs/firecat-protocol/mod.ts` -- Register the three new validators in the schema object.
- `libs/firecat-protocol/validators_test.ts` -- Add tests for all three validators.

## Testing

```bash
deno test libs/firecat-protocol/validators_test.ts
```

## Dependencies

No prerequisites. This is the foundation for the entire confirmation protocol. Blocks G2-A2-02 (confirmationValidator), G2-A2-05 (discovery loop), and G2-A2-06 (validation replay).
